help.name: help
help.text: Will present you with a list of short descriptions for other SoySource commands. You can add a particular command to recieve extended information about that command.

avatar.name: avatar
avatar.text: Sends the URL of the requester's avatar/profile picture.

ctof.name: ctof
ctof.text: Converts celsius to fahrenheit. Takes degrees celsius as input.

ftoc.name: ftoc
ftoc.text: Converts fahrenheit to celsius. Takes degrees fahrenheit as input.

kick.name: kick
kick.text: (WIP) Kicks the user given as input.

light.name: light
light.text: This command is only usable by the owner of this bot.

ping.name: ping
ping.text: Returns the bot (ping) delay in milliseconds.

time.name: time
time.text: Sends back the times for different regions and timezones in the user's preferred time format (24 hour time by default). Can be used with or without arguments.

eval.name: eval
eval.text: This command is only usable by the owner of this bot.

curcon.name: curcon
curcon.text: (WIP) Converts currency from one to another. Takes arguments in the form of `[amount] [from] [to]`

osu.name: osu
osu.text: Gives a short summary of the mentioned osu! account.
osu.exampleout:
osu! Profile for peppy (#297280) - AU
Total PP: 762.78
...
Overall Acc: 96.67%

osur.name: osur
osur.text: Gives information about the last osu! standard play by the mentioned osu! user.
osur.exampleout:
Most recent ranked play for Fikstorm:
Mods: HDHR
Star Rating: 8.62*
...
Completion: 99.24%

osub.name: osub
osub.text: Gives best osu! standard plays for a given user.
osub.exampleout:
Top 5 osu! standard plays for peppy
1. Lix - Tori no Uta (...)

aesthetic.name: aesthetic
aesthetic.text: This command is supposed to convert the text you give as an argument into  a e s t h e t i c i s e d  text, but I haven't programmed that yet.
aesthetic.exampleout: d i c k b u t t

log.name: log
log.text: Logs the given arguments to the developer console.
log.exampleout: Logged Hello future people! to console

rng.name: rng
rng.text: Generates a random number between 1 and 10.

exec.name: exec
exec.text: This command is only usable by the owner of this bot.

configchange.name: configchange
configchange.text: This command is only usable by the owner of this bot.
configchange.exmapleout: Changed the config file object `version` to `4.2.3`

restart.name: restart
restart.text: This command is only usable by the owner of this bot.

define.name: define
define.text: Define a given word using *Webster's Unabridged English Dictionary*. Note that the version of the dictionary used is not complete.
define.exampleout:
**click**
To make a slight, sharp noise (or a succession of such noises),as by gentle striking; to tick.The varnished clock that clicked behind the door. Goldsmith.

play.name: play
play.text: Play audio for a video from YouTube in a voice channel. Requesting user must be in a voice channel accessible by the bot.
play.exampleout: yOu'D bEtTeR bE gEtTiNg In A vOiCe ChAnNeL

leave.name: leave
leave.text: Leaves a voice channel, if the bot is in one.
leave.exampleout: I'm not in a voice channel, silly!

reverse.name: reverse
reverse.examplein: peppy is a lower rank than me
reverse.exampleout: em naht knar rewol a si yppep

picdump.name: picdump
picdump.text: WIP - In theory, dumps the undeleted images of a channel into a file/folder
picdump.exampleout: I mean really, I haven't even figured out what format the result is gonna be in. Maybe it'll shove the result in a folder on my web server? @mention SoySource to send suggestions for this

timereg.name: timereg
timereg.text: Allows a user to register their preferred time format (24 or 12 hour time).
timereg.exampleout: Registered 12 hour time to your account.

life.name: life
life.text:
Tells you *exactly* who doesn't have a life.
Command added at the explicit request of my lad Jack.

say.name: say
say.text:
Says a given message in the specified channel.
I mainly made this command for someone on stackoverflow, it's pretty bad.

patreon.name: patreon
patreon.text: Sends a link to my patreon page.

spongebird.name: spongebird
spongebird.text: You know that one meme with spongebob as a bird that usually has text tHaT gOeS lIkE tHiS? Yeah, this command is that.

tgp.name: tgp
tgp.text: literally just sends the :tgp: emote from the TGP server because i needed to for some testing
